  "texts": [
    "This layer only updates the single-atom f 0 i and pairatom g 0 ij representations, and does not update the equivariant pair-atom representation h ij that is of dimension 3.",
    "The repinit layer first embeds the concatenated single-and pair-atom representations to update the pairatom representation",
    "Then, we concatenate the g 0 ij and h ij pair-atom representations to recover the environment matrix and update the single-atom representation using a symmetrization operation",
    "The symmetrization operator, first introduced by ref.",
    "41, has the general form of symm (x j, y j), where x j and y j are neighbor-indexed vectors."
  ],
